When DA is added to the MIPs@ PIn-BAc/GQDs solution, the PL intensity of the MIPs@ PIn-BAc/GQDs linearly decreases with the DA concentration in the range of 5–1200nM with a correlation coefficient of R2

                        =0.9946 (Fig. 6b). And the limit of detection (LOD) for DA is as low as 2.5nM based on signal-to-noise ratio of 3. Meanwhile, the MIPs@ PIn-BAc/GQDs for DA are more sensitivity than that obtained by NIPs@ PIn-BAc/GQDs. To our knowledge, above results show superiority towards those of previous quantum dots based DA fluorescent sensors (Table 1
                        ).
